hpnicfUserLogMIB.name: hpnicfUserLogMIB
hpnicfUserLogMIB.description: The HPN-ICF-USERLOG-MIB contains objects to Manage configuration and Monitor running state for userlog feature.

hpnicfUserlogNatVersion.name: hpnicfUserlogNatVersion
hpnicfUserlogNatVersion.description: NAT LOG version. Currently only version 1 is developed.

hpnicfUserlogNatSyslog.name: hpnicfUserlogNatSyslog
hpnicfUserlogNatSyslog.description: NAT LOG format. If 1, LOG format is sysLog. If 0, LOG format is UDP packet. UDP packet is the default format, and is recommended.

hpnicfUserlogNatSourceIP.description: The Source IP address of NAT LOG UDP packet.

hpnicfUserlogNatFlowBegin.name: hpnicfUserlogNatFlowBegin
hpnicfUserlogNatFlowBegin.description: Log the NAT flow when it is created. If 1, this function is enabled. If 0, this function is disabled. This function will be used when real-time monitor required.

hpnicfUserlogNatActiveTime.name: hpnicfUserlogNatActiveTime
hpnicfUserlogNatActiveTime.description: The active time for long-time existed NAT flow. Unit: minute. Range: 10 minutes ~ 120 minutes. When setting it, NAT flow can be logged after an interval of active time. This function will be used when real-time monitor required. The default value 0 means real-time monitor function is disabled.
